1{-# LANGUAGE ScopedTypeVariables #-}
2{-# OPTIONS_GHC -Wall #-}
3
4-- | Term-content operator.
5
6module Koshucode.Baala.Data.Church.Cop
7  ( -- * Operator
8    Cop (..), CopCox, CopTree, copName, 
9  
10    -- * Operator name
11    copNormal, copInternal, copPrefix, copInfix, copPostfix,
12  
13    -- * Operator set
14    CopSet (..), CopFind, copset, copsetFill,
15  ) where
16
17import qualified Koshucode.Baala.Base             as B
18import qualified Koshucode.Baala.Syntax           as S
19import qualified Koshucode.Baala.Data.Church.Cox  as D
20
21
22-- ----------------------  Operator
23
24-- | Term-content operator.
25data Cop c
26    = CopCalc S.BlankName (D.CopCalc c) -- ^ Convert @c@ (content)
27    | CopCox  S.BlankName (CopCox c)    -- ^ Convert 'D.Cox' c
28    | CopTree S.BlankName (CopTree)     -- ^ Convert 'B.TTree'
29
30-- | Expression-level syntax.
31type CopCox c = [D.Cox c] -> B.Ab (D.Cox c)
32
33-- | Tree-level syntax.
34type CopTree  = [S.TTree] -> B.Ab S.TTree
35
36instance Show (Cop c) where
37    show (CopCalc n _) = "(CopCalc " ++ show n ++ " _)"
38    show (CopCox  n _) = "(CopCox "  ++ show n ++ " _)"
39    show (CopTree n _) = "(CopTree " ++ show n ++ " _)"
40
41instance B.Name (Cop c) where
42    name = B.name . copName
43
44copName :: Cop c -> S.BlankName
45copName (CopCalc  n _) = n
46copName (CopCox   n _) = n
47copName (CopTree  n _) = n
48
49
50-- ----------------------  Operator name
51
52-- | Name for non-binary operator.
53copNormal :: String -> S.BlankName
54copNormal = S.BlankNormal
55
56-- | Name for program-generated operator.
57copInternal :: String -> S.BlankName
58copInternal = S.BlankInternal
59
60-- | Name for prefix operator.
61copPrefix :: String -> S.BlankName
62copPrefix = S.BlankPrefix
63
64-- | Name for postfix operator.
65copPostfix :: String -> S.BlankName
66copPostfix = S.BlankPostfix
67
68-- | Name for infix operator.
69copInfix :: String -> S.BlankName
70copInfix = S.BlankInfix
71
72
73-- ----------------------  Operator set
74
75data CopSet c = CopSet
76    { copsetCopList    :: [Cop c]
77    , copsetInfixList  :: [B.Named B.InfixHeight]
78
79    , copsetCalcList   :: [B.Named (Cop c)]  -- CopCalc
80    , copsetCoxList    :: [B.Named (Cop c)]  -- CopCox
81    , copsetTreeList   :: [B.Named (Cop c)]  -- CopTree
82
83    , copsetFindCalc   :: CopFind (D.Cox c)
84    , copsetFindCox    :: CopFind (CopCox c)
85    , copsetFindTree   :: CopFind CopTree
86
87    , copsetDerived    :: [D.NamedCox c]
88    }
89
90-- | Find content operator from its name.
91type CopFind f = S.BlankName -> Maybe f
92
93-- | Empty operator set.
94copset :: CopSet c
95copset = CopSet [] [] [] [] [] find find find [] where
96    find _ = Nothing
97
98copsetFill :: B.Map (CopSet c)
99copsetFill opset = opset2 where
100
101    opset2 = opset { copsetFindCalc  =  contFind
102                   , copsetFindCox   =  coxFind
103                   , copsetFindTree  =  treeFind }
104
105    contFind    =  B.assocFinder contList
106    coxFind     =  B.assocFinder coxList
107    treeFind    =  B.assocFinder treeList
108
109    contList    =  B.catMaybes $ map cont cops
110    coxList     =  B.catMaybes $ map cox  cops
111    treeList    =  B.catMaybes $ map tree cops
112
113    cont (CopCalc n f)   =  Just (n, D.CoxCalc [] n f)
114    cont _               =  Nothing
115
116    cox (CopCox n f)     =  Just (n, f)
117    cox _                =  Nothing
118
119    tree (CopTree n f)   =  Just (n, f)
120    tree _               =  Nothing
121
122    cops  = copsetCopList opset
123
